name: Verve
arrival: When you arrive, look for the callbox, dial 083, and hit call. When prompted you will use the keypad to enter your reservation pincode: {callboxpin}. After you enter the code the front door will unlock. Head straight to the elevator and up to the 12th floor. Please do not follow anyone in - you need to be buzzed in to unlock the elevator. You will find your apartment door unlocked and the apartment keys sitting on the diningroom table. The attached fob is to access the front entrance and building amenities.
parking: Street parking in that area that is metered from 8am-8pm but otherwise free. There is also a paid parking garage directly across the street in the KOMO building garage.
amenities/commonAreas: There is a rooftop deck and gym located on the 7th floor.
amenities/trash: There is a trash room on every floor with chutes.

name: Cove

After you enter the code the front door will unlock. Head straight to the elevator and up to the 7th floor. Please do not follow anyone in - you need to be buzzed in to unlock the elevator. You will find your apartment door unlocked and the apartment keys sitting on the counter. The attached fob with two buttons is to access the front entrance and building amenities. name: Rollin Street Flats
arrival: When you arrive, look for the callbox, dial 043, and you'll be buzzed in. Head to the elevator and dial 5123 on the keypad before pressing your floor. You will find your apartment door unlocked and the apartment keys sitting on the diningroom table. The attached fob is to access the front entrance, elevator, garage, and building amenities.
parking: There is a 3rd-party managed public garage you can access after hours with your key fob. Any of the store/retail spots are available for your use. Parking ranges from $22 per day (if it is purchased before 6:00 PM) to $5 dollars for overnight parking if you purchase a spot after 6:00 PM. Follow the instructions posted near the garage entrance to pay for parking using your mobile. There is also metered street parking.
amenities/commonAreas: There is a rooftop deck accessible, a community lounge/outside grilling area on the 4th floor, and a gym on the 2nd floor.
amenities/trash: There is a trash chute on every floor to the right of the elevators.
amenities/tv: The television has cable and Google ChromeCast for streaming. Cable can be found on the HDMI 1 input.

name: Marina SLU
arrival: The entrance to Marina SLU is located at the bottom of the stairs of the breezeway on Westlake Ave N. The building is green.At the entrance you will see a callbox. Press 003 on the keypad and let it dial. It will make a quiet noise as it connects and the display will change.Press {callboxpin} on the keypad and the door will beep and unlock to give you access to the lobby.Once in the lobby please proceed to the KeyCafe to retrieve your keys. It is located in the alcove behind the wooden wall directly across from the front entrance. The wall is marked with 'Domicile Keycafe behind this wall'.Touch the screen, select pick up, confirm that all the boxes are closed, and enter access code {accesscode} when prompted to grab your keys. There is more information about key access posted on either side of the keycafe.The black and white circular fob on your keyset will give you access to the front door, the building amenities, the elevator, and your apartment door. The blue fob marked 'keycafe' is strictly used for returning your keys upon check out.If you purchased parking for your stay please reference the â€œParkingâ€ù section below for more information.Proceed down the hall passed the clubroom, bowling alley, and gym to the elevator alcove. It is behind the door at the end of the hall.To access your floor you will need to scan your apartment fob inside of the elevator. Scan the fob by touching it to the rectangular black scanner above the buttons and press your floor number when the light turns green.
parking: Parking is $20 per night and must be requested and paid for at least 24 hours before check in. An invoice will be sent to the email you provided for your reservation.The parking fob is on your key set in keycafe. The square fob with a button is for the garage.Temporarily park your car on Highland Dr, Dexter Ave, or across the street on Westlake Ave N.Enter the building from the Westlake Ave N.  The entrance is located at the bottom of the stairs of the breezeway.Retrieve your keys using the KeyCafe.Enter the garage through Highland Drive (off of Westlake Ave N) and veer left (up).Please only park in the spots marked DOMICILE RESERVED. They are first come first serve. Unmarked spots belong to other businesses and residents.Head to your apartment from the garage by using the south elevator. The door will be marked Marina SLU and is situated atop a small flight of stairs nearest parking spot 155. The elevator alcove for your building should be painted yellow. If the alcove is another color you are in the wrong building.
amenities/commonAreas: There is a club room with pool table, gym, and bowling alley available on the 1st floor of the Marina SLU building. There is an outside terrace with BBQs and an entertaining kitchen on the 7th floor. You must have your room key fob to access these areas.
amenities/trash: There is a trash room on every floor near the elevator.
departure/0: Checkout is promptly at 11:00 AM. The cleaning staff will arrive around 11:30 AM (unless agreed otherwise) to prepare for our next guest. Please be courteous of the check-out time.
departure/1: If you have time we would greatly appreciate it if you load dishes in the dishwasher and run it.
departure/2: Double check to make sure youâ€™ve collected all your personal belongings.
departure/3: Please return your key to the Keycafe on the 1st floor upon checking out. Touch the screen, select the return option, and follow the prompts to return your keys using the same Keycafe access code you used at check-in.

name: Chroma SLU
arrival: The entrance to Chroma SLU is located at 1212 Harrison St.At the entrance you will see a callbox. Dial 315 on the keypad and let it call. You will hear a series of beeps as the system dials out. Once the beeps cease, you will be prompted to enter your callbox pin code. Press {callboxpin} on the keypad (*Note that the prompt can be quiet - you do not need to wait for it to finish speaking before entering your code.)The door will beep and unlock to give you access to the lobby.Once in the lobby, please proceed to the KeyCafe to retrieve your keys. It is located on the grey column facing the elevators.Touch the screen, select pick up, confirm that all the boxes are closed, and enter access code {accesscode} when prompted to obtain your keys.The grey plastic fob on your keyset will give you access to the front door, the building amenities, the elevator, and your apartment door. The blue fob marked â€œkeycafeâ€ù is strictly used for returning your keys upon check out.If you purchased parking for your stay please reference the â€œParkingâ€ù section below for more information.To access your floor you will need to scan your apartment fob inside of the elevator. Scan the fob by touching it to the rectangular black scanner above the buttons and press your floor number when the light turns green.
parking: Parking costs $40 dollars per night and is invoiced directly to your e-mail. Parking can be requested anytime between the hours of 10 AM - 6 PM. Please be sure to provide an e-mail address for billing.Once youâ€™ve paid your invoice youâ€™ll be sent a second access code for a garage fob contained within our KeyCafe.If you are arriving for the first time, temporarily park your car on Minor Ave, Pontius Ave, Harrison St, Republican St, or the alley between the two Chroma buildings.Follow the entrance instructions detailed under Check In.Retrieve your keys using the KeyCafe. Retrieve the garage fob using the second access code provided.Enter the garage through the alley off of Harrison St.Please only park in the spots marked DOMICILE RESERVED. They are stalls 137-144 and 150-157 on level P2. They are first come first serve. Unmarked spots belong to other businesses and residents.
amenities/trash: The trash room is located directly next to apartment 315 (on the 3rd floor), 415 (on the 4th floor), and 515 (on the 5th floor). The chute on the left side is for the trash. Press the red button to open the door and place all bagged trash in the chute. The chute will automatically close within ten seconds of opening.
departure/0: Checkout is promptly at 11:00 AM. The cleaning staff will arrive around 11:30 AM (unless agreed otherwise) to prepare for our next guest. Please be courteous of the check-out time.
departure/1: If you have time, we would greatly appreciate it if you load dishes in the dishwasher and run it.
departure/2: Double check to make sure youâ€™ve collected all your personal belongings. Domicile is not responsible for lost items.
departure/3: Please return your key to the KeyCcafe on the 1st floor upon checking out. Touch the screen, select the return option, and follow the prompts to return your keys. You will scan the blue KeyCafe fob in the slot on the side of the box prior to dropping them in a box.
amenities/gym: There is a gym located on the 1st floor to the right of the entrance. It can be accessed using the building key fob.
amenities/clubroom: There is a clubroom on the 2nd floor with pool table, televisions, seating area, and outside patio. To access the space exit elevator onto the 2nd floor and turn left.  The Clubhouse will be the first door directly after the mural. Can be accessed using the building key fob.
amenities/roofdeck: The roof deck has a first come, first serve BBQ, pet run, and a sitting area. To access it select floor 'R' in the elevator and exit through the door directly outside the elevator on the â€œRâ€ù level.
amenities/recycle: The trash room is located directly next to apartment 315 (on the 3rd floor), 415 (on the 4th floor), and 515 (on the 5th floor). The chute on the right side is for the recycling. Press the red button to open the door and place all bagged recycling in the chute. All cardboard boxes must be properly broken down. The chute will automatically close within ten seconds of opening.
departure/4: If you received parking during your stay you will want pull your car out of the garage and temporarily park it on Minor Ave, Pontius Ave, Harrison St, Republican St, or the alley between the two Chroma buildings prior to returning your keys.
